## Non-negotiables
- **Never call `fetch` inside a component.** All API access goes through `src/lib/api.ts`.
- **All shared types live in `src/types/index.ts`** and must mirror the backend JSON contract.
- **Server Components by default.** Add `"use client"` only when a file needs hooks, event
  handlers, or browser APIs.
- **Build UI from shadcn primitives in `src/components/ui/`** — don't hand-roll buttons, inputs,
  cards, dialogs with raw Tailwind when a `ui/` component exists.
- **Use semantic color tokens** (`bg-background`, `text-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`, …),
  never hardcoded palette values like `sky-600` / `slate-900`.

## Backend contract (the API this app talks to)
- Base URL from `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` (default `http://localhost:5065`). Routes are under `/api`.
- JSON is **camelCase**. Enums are **strings** (status `"Pending" | "Confirmed" | "Cancelled" | "Completed"`).
- Times are `"HH:mm"` or `"HH:mm:ss"` strings; dates are `"YYYY-MM-DD"` strings.
- Error responses look like `{ code, message }`; validation errors like `{ message, errors: { field: string[] } }`.
